             ## SOURCE FILES

-            Read these pre-fetched Bluesky JSON files from data/bluesky/:
+            Two distinct response shapes — handle both. If a file is missing,
+            empty, or contains zero posts, just skip it; do NOT fail the run.
+
+            **searchPosts shape** (4 files, top-level `{"posts": [...]}`):
             - data/bluesky/ai_announcements.json
             - data/bluesky/llm_releases.json
             - data/bluesky/model_discussions.json
             - data/bluesky/ml_papers.json
-            - data/bluesky/karpathy.json
-
-            The Bluesky JSON structure is:
-            - posts[].author.handle (username like "user.bsky.social")
-            - posts[].author.displayName (display name)
-            - posts[].record.text (post content)
-            - posts[].record.createdAt (ISO timestamp)
-            - posts[].likeCount (likes)
-            - posts[].repostCount (reposts)
-            - posts[].uri (post URI for linking)
+
+            **getAuthorFeed shape** (5 files, top-level `{"feed": [{"post": {...}}, ...]}`):
+            - data/bluesky/karpathy.json        (Andrej Karpathy)
+            - data/bluesky/rasbt.json           (Sebastian Raschka)
+            - data/bluesky/simonwillison.json   (Simon Willison)
+            - data/bluesky/emollick.json        (Ethan Mollick)
+            - data/bluesky/sama.json            (Sam Altman)
+
+            For searchPosts, iterate `posts[]`. For getAuthorFeed, iterate
+            `feed[].post` to get the same shape. Each `post` object has:
+            - author.handle (username like "user.bsky.social")
+            - author.displayName (display name)
+            - record.text (post content)
+            - record.createdAt (ISO timestamp)
+            - likeCount (likes)
+            - repostCount (reposts)
+            - uri (post URI for linking)

             To create a link: https://bsky.app/profile/{handle}/post/{post_id}
             Where post_id is the last segment of the uri (after "app.bsky.feed.post/")
